		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Perhaps Nintendo never acted on this because a lot of the features that a second PPU would provide could be done just as easily with hardware on the cartridge that blasts pixels to the regular PPU. (See: Wide Boy and Super FX.) I still believe it's possible to make a TV tuner for the NES, which would allow Xbox 360 level graphics.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


